This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for relation classification in medical records. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel architecture that combines CNN and RNN models, which are popular in the fields of deep learning and neural networks. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on two clinical datasets, which could make it relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
